text: Aleksandr Dobrzhansky (19 April 1873 - 15 November 1937) was a Georgian sports shooter. He competed in seven events at the 1912 Summer Olympics, representing the Russian Empire. ==References== Category:1873 births Category:1937 deaths Category:Russian male sport shooters Category:Olympic shooters of Russia Category:Shooters at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Tbilisi
